-- Warner Music buying majority stake in Roadrunner
-- 
-- Mon Dec 18, 2006 7:17am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/18/us-warnermusic-roadrunner-idUSWEN127020061218

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Warner Music Group Corp. WMG.N said on Monday it will acquire 73.5 percent of Roadrunner Music Group B.V., which includes Roadrunner Records, one of the leading hard rock labels, for about $73.5 million. 

 Warner Music Group said Roadrunner's managing director, Cees Wessels, will continue to run the company he founded, and there will be no staff changes as part of the acquisition.